%N A143461 Square array A(n,k) of numbers of length n quaternary words with at least k 0-digits between any other digits (n,k >= 0), read by antidiagonals.
%H A143461 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A143461/b143461.txt">Antidiagonals n = 0..140, flattened</a>
%F A143461 G.f. of column k: 1/(x^k*(1-x-3*x^(k+1))).
%F A143461 A(n,k) = 4^n if k=0, else A(n,k) = 3*n+1 if n<=k+1, else A(n,k) = A(n-1,k) + 3*A(n-k-1,k).
%e A143461 A (3,1) = 19, because 19 quaternary words of length 3 have at least 1 0-digit between any other digits: 000, 001, 002, 003, 010, 020, 030, 100, 101, 102, 103, 200, 201, 202, 203, 300, 301, 301, 303.
